The '''Greater Han''' is a [[school of thought]], "which holds that all the inhabitants of [[China]] belong to one (Chinese) family, and that incidental differences of [[culture]], [[religion]] and [[language]] are unfortunate aberrations, destined to be subsumed in a 'Greater [[Han Chinese|Han]]' Chinese whole."<ref>Forbes, Warlords, 163f</ref>
